nts. It's a puzzling situation that needs careful thought!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test coverage**\\n\\nI'm considering how the external workflow might only run the newly generated test class for active classes. There’s something about GcmSpecUtilTest having a direct call that seems important. If there's no coverage, it could be due to the test not being included in the native image, likely tied to the class name.\\n\\nI think I can enhance this by using the public API of `Cipher.getParameters()` after AES/GCM encryption. I'll look into how dynamic-access reporting interacts with the caller in the library versus the tests. It's complicated but interesting!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring GCMParameterSpec issues**\\n\\nI'm thinking that maybe the agent is filtering out `javax.crypto.spec.GCMParameterSpec` since the user-code-filter only includes `org.bouncycastle`. It's possible the dynamic access report is showing an active class from BouncyCastle. \\n\\nI wonder if `GCMParameterSpec` gets initialized at build-time in JDK 21. If `GcmSpecUtil.gcmSpecExtractable` returns false in native, that could lead to a NullPointerException when the constructor is called. I should check if in Native Image, `ClassUtil.loadClass` for `GCMParameterSpec` is returning null.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QW7QkimeX0xX31vc6ZtbvQPv|fc_0fd0aa56a7d488b6016a268b2e19cc8197936df502e6b4c3f5", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/main/extracted/org/bouncycastle/jcajce/provider/symmetric/util/ClassUtil.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 532, "output": 991, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44531, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780910868318, "responseId": "resp_0fd0aa56a7d488b6016a268b14d40081979573dc3ca1a150